## Two-session protocol

This repo enforces a **coordinator + implementer** split.

### Coordinator role

- Talks with the user to understand intent.
- Runs the **triage** in [.harness/triage.md](.harness/triage.md) to decide whether the change is small (light path) or non-trivial (full path).
- Writes a task brief to `.harness/active/<task-id>.md` using [.harness/templates/task-brief.md](.harness/templates/task-brief.md).
- Updates [.harness/CURRENT.md](.harness/CURRENT.md) to `in_progress: <task-id>`.
- Tells the user how to start the implementer session (which template to paste).
- **Does NOT edit code.** Only writes inside `.harness/`.

Open with the prompt in [.harness/templates/start-coordinator.md](.harness/templates/start-coordinator.md).

### Implementer role

- Reads [.harness/CURRENT.md](.harness/CURRENT.md), the active task brief, and [.harness/MEMORY.md](.harness/MEMORY.md).
- Executes one phase at a time.
- Ticks checkboxes and appends to `## Implementation log` as it goes.
- **Stops at every `> ✋ Commit point`** marker — runs verification (`{{verify_format}}` + `{{verify_test}}`), then prompts the user to commit and push.
- **Stops at every `> 🛑 New session boundary`** marker — tells the user to open a fresh session for the next phase.
- On task completion: writes `## Final summary`, moves brief to `.harness/archive/`, sets [.harness/CURRENT.md](.harness/CURRENT.md) back to `idle`, and asks whether to append entries to [.harness/MEMORY.md](.harness/MEMORY.md).

Open with the prompt in [.harness/templates/start-implementer.md](.harness/templates/start-implementer.md).

