## Branch model

```
{{branch_feature_prefix}}<task-id> ──(free merge)──→ {{branch_dev}}{{#has_dev_branch}}          # {{branch_dev}} = staging/test sandbox{{/has_dev_branch}}
{{branch_feature_prefix}}<task-id> ──(PR + template)──→ {{branch_main}}      # {{branch_main}} = protected; PR template required
```

- `{{branch_feature_prefix}}* → {{branch_dev}}` is for testing only; merge freely, no template.{{^has_dev_branch}}  (No dev branch configured; this row does not apply.){{/has_dev_branch}}
- `{{branch_feature_prefix}}* → {{branch_main}}` requires the PR template at [.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md](.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md). Self-merge is allowed (the template's protocol-status field carries the discipline).{{#has_dev_branch}}
- There is **no `{{branch_dev}} → {{branch_main}}` flow** — {{branch_dev}} is throwaway.{{/has_dev_branch}}

Forbidden:

- `git push --force` to `{{branch_main}}`
- `git commit --no-verify` to bypass the phase commit verification
- Skipping phase commit point checks

